Package: CEACT
Title: Cost-Effectiveness Analysis Toolkit for Clinical Trials
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Imad",
           family = "EL BADISY",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "elbadisyimad@gmail.com")
Description: CEACT (Cost-Effectiveness Analysis Toolkit for Clinical Trials) is a comprehensive R package designed to facilitate the economic evaluation of healthcare interventions within the context of clinical trials. It offers a suite of analytical tools and models to assess the cost-effectiveness of medical treatments, integrating both clinical outcomes and economic considerations. The package supports various types of cost-effectiveness analyses, including incremental cost-effectiveness ratios (ICERs) and cost-utility analyses (CUAs).
